ABUJA – Senator Ali-Modu Sheriff, a leading aspirant for the Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has declared his readiness to abide by any position President Mohammadu Buhari may take on the choice of APC Chairman. He said his decision to offer himself to serve as Chairman of APC was predicated on the capacity he believes he has to lead the party to victory again in 2023. That aside he said he will support whoever the president chooses to lead the party. BREAKING: Enyinnaya Harbor, Abia APC Chairman Is Dead Why APC Needs Rugged, Experienced Candidate As Chairman –… Details later.